<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="faq__title">ThesisArcPro Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq__list">

      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__question">
          Can you help me find a research consultant for my specific subject?
          <span class="faq__arrow">▾</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq__answer">
          <p>Yes, our consultancy service connects you with experts across 30+ disciplines. We specialize in matching your specific research topic with a consultant who has the academic background and technical expertise to guide your work to success.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__question">
          Is ThesisArcPro research consultancy legal?
          <span class="faq__arrow">▾</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq__answer">
          <p>Yes, our services are structured as legitimate academic research mentorship. We provide expert guidance, structural support, and methodological advice to help you navigate your academic requirements safely and ethically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__question">
          Is it safe to engage a research consultant?
          <span class="faq__arrow">▾</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq__answer">
          <p>Your privacy is our highest priority. All interactions, data sharing, and research files are kept strictly confidential and anonymous, ensuring your academic work and personal information remain secure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__question">
          How fast can you assist with my thesis or dissertation?
          <span class="faq__arrow">▾</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq__answer">
          <p>We specialize in delivering high-quality research guidance even under tight deadlines. Whether you need help with a proposal or a final chapter polish, we work with you to ensure your milestones are met on time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.faq {
  background: var(--bg-body, #ffffff);
  padding: 3.5rem 0;
  border-top: 1px solid #eef2f7;
}
.faq__title {
  font-family: var(--font-heading, 'Poppins', sans-serif);
  font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.6rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-main, #303b4f);
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.faq__list {
  max-width: 720px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0;
}

.faq__item {
  border-bottom: 1px solid #eef2f7;
}
.faq__item:first-child {
  border-top: 1px solid #eef2f7;
}

.faq__question {
  width: 100%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 1.1rem 0;
  background: none;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: var(--font-body, 'Poppins', sans-serif);
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-main, #303b4f);
  text-align: left;
  line-height: 1.4;
  transition: color 0.2s;
}
.faq__question:hover {
  color: var(--color-secondary, #046fcd);
}

.faq__arrow {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--color-main-light, #6d7483);
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
.faq__item.open .faq__arrow {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.faq__answer {
  display: none;
  padding: 0 0 1.1rem;
}
.faq__item.open .faq__answer {
  display: block;
}
.faq__answer p {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  color: var(--color-main-light, #6d7483);
  line-height: 1.7;
  padding-left: 0.5rem;
  border-left: 2px solid var(--color-secondary-lightest, #eef6fb);
}
</style>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq__question').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const item = btn.closest('.faq__item');
      const wasOpen = item?.classList.contains('open');

      // Close all
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq__item.open').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('open'));

      // Toggle clicked
      if (!wasOpen) item?.classList.add('open');
    });
  });
</script>
